11:51.720 --> 11:54.223
<i>Of course they were
gonna try to kill me.</i>

11:54.305 --> 11:56.854
<i>Death is what
they do for a living.</i>

11:59.644 --> 12:00.941
(STONE SHIFTING)

12:02.313 --> 12:04.611
<i>So the question
ain't ”What happened?”</i>

12:05.400 --> 12:06.947
<i>The question is</i>

12:09.362 --> 12:11.035
<i>"What happened to me?”</i>

12:23.835 --> 12:25.007
(WOMAN MOANS)

12:29.382 --> 12:31.384
You are
the Lord Marshal now.

12:32.802 --> 12:34.975
<i>How did they get so close?</i>

12:38.808 --> 12:41.812
<i>How did I let them
blindside me like that?</i>

12:42.479 --> 12:45.153
CROWD: Threshold!
Take us to the threshold!

12:46.191 --> 12:47.989
<i>RIDDICK:
Necromongers.</i>

12:48.860 --> 12:51.488
<i>Some wanted to put
a crown on my head.</i>

12:53.656 --> 12:56.500
<i>Some wanted to put
a noose around my neck.</i>

12:59.496 --> 13:01.965
<i>Okay, more nooses than crowns.</i>

13:05.335 --> 13:07.178
<i>I needed a way out.</i>

13:09.255 --> 13:11.178
<i>Some new place.</i>

13:13.093 --> 13:16.188
<i>Or maybe just an old one.</i>

13:21.476 --> 13:24.446
<i>But how do you find something
you've never seen?</i>

13:26.564 --> 13:29.534
Please, come back to bed.

14:01.057 --> 14:04.061
Sometimes I think you never
sleep, Lord Marshal.

14:06.271 --> 14:09.070
How can I sleep
when I have so many...

14:09.440 --> 14:11.067
Distractions?

14:12.485 --> 14:16.911
So what is the best way
to a man's heart?

14:18.658 --> 14:20.706
Between the fourth
and fifth rib.

14:22.245 --> 14:23.918
That's where I usually go.

14:26.124 --> 14:28.923
I'll put a twist at the end
if I wanna make sure.

14:31.087 --> 14:35.763
They'll never let you stand at the threshold
of Underverse without embracing the faith.

14:36.342 --> 14:40.313
That's why they come
after you, these assassins.

14:41.347 --> 14:43.816
They think of you
as something wrong.

14:44.267 --> 14:47.567
Cursed.
Illegitimate.

14:50.106 --> 14:52.609
What are you gonna do
when you're born that way?

14:53.276 --> 14:54.823
(RUSTLING)
(GASPS)

14:57.030 --> 14:58.031
Did you hear?

15:00.533 --> 15:02.376
Do you think the guards
are still there?

15:13.796 --> 15:15.298
Lord Marshal!

15:18.134 --> 15:19.761
Something like that?

15:33.191 --> 15:35.660
I said between
the fourth and fifth.

15:37.987 --> 15:41.491
Fifth and sixth?
Body cavity.

15:43.076 --> 15:44.077
(GASPS)

15:49.499 --> 15:50.500
(THUDS)

15:55.713 --> 15:57.340
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

16:03.388 --> 16:05.311
Making more friends,
I see.

16:06.391 --> 16:07.813
But who put her up to it?

16:08.893 --> 16:10.520
Which commander?

16:12.021 --> 16:13.614
It could be any of many.

16:15.525 --> 16:17.277
Don't doubt it for a second,

16:18.945 --> 16:20.162
Commander Vaako.

16:22.115 --> 16:23.367
Lord Marshal.

16:32.500 --> 16:34.343
They say you lost
your nerve, Vaako,

16:36.170 --> 16:38.343
after that big swing
and a miss.

16:40.550 --> 16:42.552
Is that what they say?

16:46.180 --> 16:48.729
Now what are you gonna
do to get that cred back?

16:50.560 --> 16:52.107
What's the big play?

16:54.230 --> 16:55.823
Something splashy.

17:00.653 --> 17:01.654
Actually,

17:02.822 --> 17:05.415
I had in mind
something different.

17:13.124 --> 17:16.502
I've been thinking
about an early campaign.

17:17.712 --> 17:20.590
My very first.
I was but a boy.

17:22.090 --> 17:25.060
We dropped from the sky
and did what Necromongers do.

17:27.221 --> 17:30.896
Destruction was breathtaking.

17:33.436 --> 17:35.279
But then we met resistance.

17:36.898 --> 17:39.401
Ferocious like
a storm of lions.

17:42.278 --> 17:45.282
Each one of them killed
over a hundred Necro

17:46.115 --> 17:47.958
before their weapons failed.

17:50.787 --> 17:53.040
And then they killed
another 30 more.

17:53.956 --> 17:55.208
Barehanded.

17:57.710 --> 18:00.634
Our firepower
and strength in numbers

18:00.755 --> 18:02.553
eventually won us the day.

18:03.966 --> 18:07.891
I can still see him, the last
of those magnificent warriors,

18:08.388 --> 18:10.311
standing on a pile
of his own.

18:12.809 --> 18:14.527
And he looked at me.

18:18.064 --> 18:21.113
And I will never
forget those eyes.

18:28.157 --> 18:31.752
His eyes were just like yours.

18:36.499 --> 18:39.343
The planet was Furya.

18:40.211 --> 18:42.384
I know what it's called.

18:43.131 --> 18:45.225
You just don't
know where it is.

18:45.716 --> 18:48.185
I need charts. I need maps.

18:48.302 --> 18:50.054
Impossible.
I need a direction.

18:50.138 --> 18:52.266
Purged from all records,
as you well know.

18:52.348 --> 18:54.021
But you remember where.

18:57.854 --> 18:59.197
So many worlds...

19:01.274 --> 19:03.823
The only map left in existence

19:04.610 --> 19:08.535
is the one that's
in my head, Riddick.

19:14.537 --> 19:16.414
So what do you want?

19:17.790 --> 19:19.292
The crown?

19:24.213 --> 19:26.056
Transcendence.

19:30.303 --> 19:31.304
Krone.

19:32.513 --> 19:34.186
Break off a ship.

19:35.725 --> 19:37.568
Riddick's going home.

19:39.812 --> 19:41.439
<i>RIDDICK:
Transcendence.</i>

19:42.565 --> 19:47.822
<i>I guess that was Necro speak for "Get the
fuck off our ship and make it forever."</i>

19:48.905 --> 19:50.248
<i>Fine by me.</i>

19:54.994 --> 19:57.838
<i>You can't blame him
for dangling Furya.</i>

19:59.081 --> 20:01.175
<i>Home has a certain equity.</i>

20:04.378 --> 20:08.178
<i>But I do blame him
for what came next.</i>

20:23.105 --> 20:25.233
It's along way to come.

20:26.067 --> 20:27.410
For this.

20:28.903 --> 20:32.203
<i>RIDDICK: This guy with
the fucked-up face, Krone,</i>

20:32.907 --> 20:35.626
<i>he was supposed to
be our ride home.</i>

20:37.703 --> 20:42.675
<i>But instead of Furya,
we wind up someplace called...</i>

20:42.750 --> 20:43.751
(SNIFFS)

20:43.834 --> 20:45.507
<i>Not Furya.</i>

20:54.595 --> 20:57.769
<i>Yet again, someone
was trying to play me.</i>

21:00.268 --> 21:01.736
<i>So yet again,</i>

21:04.230 --> 21:06.028
<i>we play for blood.</i>

