39:59.364 --> 40:00.707
Nothing.

40:03.034 --> 40:04.877
Look again, Diaz.

40:08.540 --> 40:11.544
Somebody should teach this
Riddick asshole how to count.

40:11.835 --> 40:16.181
"Leave one ship"? Like we've got
a fucking spare laying around.

40:16.756 --> 40:18.383
Let's crank it up.

40:19.217 --> 40:20.218
(WHIRRING)

40:29.269 --> 40:31.397
Good morning, Cyclops.

40:46.202 --> 40:48.125
(SHIP POWERING DOWN)

40:55.295 --> 40:56.421
Hey, Luna.

40:59.299 --> 41:00.391
Yeah.

41:00.925 --> 41:02.302
Wake her up,
kick her out of bed.

41:03.094 --> 41:04.596
What do you mean?

41:04.929 --> 41:06.556
We're running heavy.

41:06.931 --> 41:08.478
She's a prisoner. Wasn't she
gonna pay our way back?

41:08.558 --> 41:10.276
We're going
big now.

41:10.643 --> 41:13.943
Okay?
Cut that 60 kilos loose.

41:20.612 --> 41:21.613
(HISSING)

41:25.283 --> 41:26.284
(WHIRRS)

41:28.787 --> 41:29.959
(WHIRRS)

41:30.455 --> 41:31.957
Get away!
Get away from me!

41:32.081 --> 41:33.549
Stop, just stop!

41:33.625 --> 41:35.252
What do you want now?

41:35.335 --> 41:38.088
I'm gonna take off
the restraints. Okay?

41:39.964 --> 41:41.181
I don't want them off.

41:41.257 --> 41:42.304
No, it's not like that.

41:43.301 --> 41:45.019
Nobody is gonna
touch you now.

41:45.428 --> 41:47.271
Santana's head is
into other stuff now.

41:48.807 --> 41:50.354
Your lucky day.
(WHIRRS)

41:52.185 --> 41:53.186
(GROANS)

41:55.104 --> 41:56.105
(WHIRRS)

41:57.148 --> 41:58.491
Get the fuck away from me.

41:58.650 --> 41:59.993
Okay.

42:01.110 --> 42:03.078
What planet is this?
Where are we?

42:03.154 --> 42:04.781
It's got air and water.
That's all you've got to know.

42:10.161 --> 42:12.084
But how am I supposed to survive...
Just go.

42:13.164 --> 42:14.632
Before he changes his mind.

42:20.630 --> 42:22.007
(PANTING)

42:27.220 --> 42:28.221
(GRUNTS)

42:29.514 --> 42:31.061
(GUNSHOT)
(GROANS)

42:40.525 --> 42:42.778
I was getting attached to her.

42:45.405 --> 42:47.453
Now where is my box at?

42:53.371 --> 42:54.372
(GASPING)

43:10.388 --> 43:13.392
The name is Santana!

43:14.601 --> 43:17.400
Shot-caller for
this crew right here!

43:18.646 --> 43:21.069
I am the guy who knows all,

43:21.566 --> 43:24.490
sees all, beats all...

43:25.570 --> 43:28.323
Spitting it kind
of strong, ain't he?

43:29.073 --> 43:30.916
Got to bait the trap.

43:31.326 --> 43:35.672
I've come all this way
to collect your head in a box!

43:35.914 --> 43:37.541
Right here!

43:39.000 --> 43:41.128
So have yourself
a fine day now,

43:41.210 --> 43:43.133
Mr. Richard B. Riddick!

43:44.297 --> 43:45.674
I suspect

43:46.841 --> 43:50.812
it will be one
of your very last!

43:51.596 --> 43:55.772
Yeah, well, you don't need to agitate
Riddick any more than, you know.

43:57.143 --> 44:00.613
Any more than bringing his
head back in a box would?

44:02.440 --> 44:03.692
(GASPING)

44:07.236 --> 44:08.738
(GASPING STOPS)

44:20.959 --> 44:22.882
(SPACESHIP APPROACHING)

44:25.922 --> 44:29.802
Shit.
Here comes the neighborhood.

44:34.973 --> 44:36.475
Small world.

44:39.560 --> 44:41.107
(DEVICE BEEPING)

44:44.691 --> 44:48.616
Unidentified vessel, this is
Clan Vagos out of Ursa Five.

44:48.820 --> 44:50.948
Be advised that we
are on the ground now

44:51.030 --> 44:53.408
and have responded to
an emergency signal.

44:53.533 --> 44:57.037
No distress found,
no need to land.

44:57.662 --> 45:02.338
I repeat, there is no reason for you
to land at this location at this time.

45:02.750 --> 45:03.967
<i>Is that clear?</i>

