<i>No reason for you to land at
this location at this time.</i>

45:10.717 --> 45:12.890
What the fuck
did I just say?

45:30.403 --> 45:32.531
It was a long haul.
We could take on some water.

45:34.032 --> 45:36.455
Wouldn't mind a little
true-gravity time either.

45:36.909 --> 45:40.209
Like I was saying,
I've got this.

45:46.753 --> 45:50.257
You knew who that was, right?
On the emergency beacon?

45:52.675 --> 45:54.268
Wouldn't be here
if I didn't.

45:56.345 --> 45:58.768
The concept of back-up
still has no appeal to you?

45:59.182 --> 46:01.731
My besties here
can ball with anyone.

46:02.226 --> 46:04.069
No disrespect for
your crew, of course,

46:04.145 --> 46:08.150
who look strong, too,
in those matchy-matchy outfits.

46:08.232 --> 46:09.199
(SANTANA'S CREW CHUCKLES)

46:09.275 --> 46:11.573
Shit. Didn't know
there was a dress code.

46:12.153 --> 46:13.200
Yeah, right?

46:13.488 --> 46:16.583
BOSS: Well, it's not my intention
to jump another man's claim.

46:17.158 --> 46:18.751
If you don't mind, maybe
we'll just pull up a chair

46:18.826 --> 46:20.544
and spectate for a while.

46:22.163 --> 46:23.585
What if I do?

46:24.165 --> 46:27.419
Well, this is a co-op station, pal.
It's open to all Mercs.

46:28.920 --> 46:31.469
By the way, my name is...
"Too late."

46:31.672 --> 46:34.642
That's your name.
"Too Late."

46:35.510 --> 46:38.184
And I don't need you stepping all
over my dick here, my friend.

46:39.305 --> 46:41.148
Well, I'll tell you what.

46:42.016 --> 46:46.271
I won't lift a finger to help until
you come ask me for it. How's that?

46:52.151 --> 46:53.494
(MAP BEEPING)

47:03.287 --> 47:05.210
I was scoping
this out earlier.

47:05.331 --> 47:07.299
It's a cave system.
Five clicks south.

47:08.000 --> 47:09.172
Might be worth a look.

47:10.503 --> 47:12.130
Hey, Too Late.

47:12.630 --> 47:14.303
Need to pull a node
from your ship

47:14.465 --> 47:16.138
and store it right here
next to mine. Okay?

47:16.217 --> 47:17.719
Really? Why is that?

47:17.802 --> 47:21.272
Riddick triggered the beacon
to get off-world, right?

47:21.806 --> 47:25.902
Basically,
he was calling a taxi.

47:27.645 --> 47:28.942
And...

47:29.397 --> 47:31.991
And a ship would make
a sweet trap, right?

47:32.316 --> 47:36.366
Confined space,
metal walls, jail cell.

47:37.697 --> 47:38.869
Is cool, huh?

47:39.157 --> 47:40.830
Is it true half
the people you meet

47:40.908 --> 47:42.581
are below average
intelligence?

47:42.660 --> 47:45.413
Got to make sure the ship stays
grounded when he comes for them, okay?

47:45.496 --> 47:47.214
(CLAPS HANDS) Come on.

47:47.665 --> 47:50.509
Dahl, pull a node
from the ship.

47:57.508 --> 47:59.681
(SHIP POWERS DOWN)

48:15.193 --> 48:16.285
I'll do it...

48:16.360 --> 48:17.407
Ooh!

48:17.486 --> 48:18.487
Ooh...

48:18.863 --> 48:19.864
(CHUCKLES)

48:28.372 --> 48:30.249
(CLICKING AND BEEPING)

48:37.965 --> 48:39.888
SANTANA:
Any time now, Riddick.

49:03.658 --> 49:05.581
I'm telling you,
this is total overkill.

49:05.743 --> 49:07.620
What? Eleven of us
out here now?

49:08.120 --> 49:10.623
Should have been
a four-man op, tops.

49:10.873 --> 49:13.717
You are jinxing our janx, man.
And that ain't cool.

49:13.793 --> 49:17.172
Hey, I don't give a shit what they say.
He's one guy.

49:19.548 --> 49:21.266
Whatever you say, man.

49:22.093 --> 49:23.766
He's one guy.

49:27.098 --> 49:28.270
MOSS: Man...

49:39.068 --> 49:41.992
So I guess that's what passes for
a fucking moon on this planet.

49:43.281 --> 49:45.375
It's gonna be
a dark night.

49:45.950 --> 49:47.497
Advantage, him.

49:48.786 --> 49:52.836
Maybe he's gonna wear you down first.
Force you to go without sleep.

49:52.915 --> 49:54.792
Can't you see I'm busy?

49:55.751 --> 49:57.845
I'm just sharing my thoughts.

49:57.920 --> 50:00.594
Well, now that you have,

50:02.300 --> 50:04.553
can I politely invite you to

50:04.635 --> 50:07.058
step off my fucking porch?

50:09.765 --> 50:11.688
I'll start rotating down.

50:11.767 --> 50:13.189
You let me know, huh?

50:13.269 --> 50:16.899
As soon as I have his head in
a box, I will let you know.

50:30.536 --> 50:32.914
(BEEPING)

50:41.505 --> 50:43.678
Grid 29D.
Stand by, stand by.

50:48.804 --> 50:50.431
DIAZ ON RADIO:
What you got, cuz?

50:52.308 --> 50:55.733
Aha, some dingo-dongo thing.

50:56.145 --> 50:57.271
(SIGHS)

50:59.357 --> 51:01.826
Yeah. I see it now.

51:02.318 --> 51:03.410
<i>You want me to pop it?</i>

51:03.486 --> 51:06.035
Knock it down.
One shot suppressed.

51:11.118 --> 51:13.712
Nice work, Diaz.
Encouraging.

51:14.622 --> 51:16.295
Had something in my eye.

51:16.749 --> 51:18.342
SANTANA: <i>It's called a scope.</i>
(SNICKERS)

51:18.501 --> 51:20.094
<i>Try next time.</i>

51:20.336 --> 51:21.883
<i>BOSS: You got this, right?</i>

51:23.130 --> 51:25.724
Will you get off
my freaking frequency!

51:27.009 --> 51:28.352
(SNIFFING)

51:38.479 --> 51:39.901
(BEEPING)

51:49.532 --> 51:51.000
What the fuck
is going on here?

52:09.135 --> 52:11.263
(POWERS DOWN)

52:13.431 --> 52:15.183
<i>VARGAS:
Thank fucking God!</i>

52:15.933 --> 52:17.230
Fuck off!

52:20.020 --> 52:23.900
Rubio, coming your way now.
Gotta swap out a bad sensor.

52:27.945 --> 52:30.448
What was here
versus what was found.

52:30.781 --> 52:32.454
How does it square?

52:32.533 --> 52:34.376
Pretty good. I mean,
the morphine's gone,

52:34.452 --> 52:37.126
but that's always
the first thing to go.

52:37.913 --> 52:40.007
That was a bit weird, though.

52:40.875 --> 52:44.049
"A predator restraint
with 42-inch offset jaws."

52:44.462 --> 52:46.590
Six listed, zero found.

52:47.381 --> 52:49.759
That is an odd thing
to go for a walk.

52:50.092 --> 52:52.845
Yeah, but, Boss, you know how shit
goes missing from these stations.

52:52.928 --> 52:56.148
One bad year and guys are
ripping shit off for salvage.

53:04.482 --> 53:05.950
Hey, Santana?

53:06.734 --> 53:09.237
You did sweep the area
before I got here, right?

53:09.570 --> 53:11.288
Sweep for what?

53:11.572 --> 53:13.791
<i>BOSS: I just want to make sure
no one has set any traps for us.</i>

53:13.866 --> 53:15.118
5Q.

53:18.078 --> 53:19.671
Understand what I'm saying?

53:19.872 --> 53:22.045
Traps?
What kind of traps?

53:22.500 --> 53:24.093
<i>The kind with jaws.</i>

53:24.168 --> 53:25.169
(METAL CLANKS)

53:31.217 --> 53:32.890
Don't touch
that fucking thing!

53:39.350 --> 53:40.351
What?

53:44.563 --> 53:45.610
Up-armor.

53:47.816 --> 53:48.817
(SIGHS)

53:55.366 --> 53:56.413
(SCREAMS)

53:56.492 --> 53:57.539
Shit!

53:57.868 --> 53:59.370
Ready. Ready.

54:02.456 --> 54:05.380
(SCREAMING) Stay put, stay
put, stay put, stay put!

54:08.963 --> 54:10.180
Oopah!

54:14.843 --> 54:17.642
<i>NUNEZ: Who the hell was
that screaming and why?</i>

54:19.390 --> 54:22.735
Nunez, break out
the sweep gear.

54:23.727 --> 54:27.152
And figure out how many
of these big-ass traps

54:27.231 --> 54:29.199
we got out here, okay?

54:30.276 --> 54:32.654
I'm thinking maybe
the whole upper left quad

54:32.778 --> 54:35.122
is some kind of
fucking mine field.

54:35.656 --> 54:37.909
You got to do that now,
okay, Nunez?

54:39.910 --> 54:41.537
<i>Copy that, Nunez?</i>

54:46.208 --> 54:47.755
Nunez?

54:49.837 --> 54:52.431
This is bad.
This is very bad.

54:54.592 --> 54:55.889
FALCO: Nunez?
Nunez?

54:55.968 --> 54:57.436
Shut the fuck up, <i>puto!</i>

54:57.511 --> 55:00.105
His radio just crapped out.
Someone get eyes on him.

55:00.472 --> 55:03.521
<i>Make sure he's right where he
should be, 13-H. Go, go, go!</i>

55:10.816 --> 55:11.942
Right here.

55:12.026 --> 55:14.154
13-H. He's supposed
to be right fucking...

55:20.659 --> 55:24.163
So this was overkill, huh?
Eleven of us, too many. Yeah.

55:24.246 --> 55:26.089
You know all
about Riddick, right?

55:26.290 --> 55:29.089
Well, maybe you need
to take that shit back!

55:29.293 --> 55:32.263
Take the jinx off our janx.
You understand me?

55:32.963 --> 55:34.590
That's what you
need to do, Falco.

55:34.673 --> 55:37.517
You need to unjinxelate
our fucking janx!

55:44.642 --> 55:46.736
Don't mess with me now.

55:48.854 --> 55:49.946
Hey. Hey, what is it?
What is it?

55:50.022 --> 55:51.239
Get back!
It's me, it's me.

55:51.315 --> 55:52.737
He's got Falco!

56:01.575 --> 56:03.794
Jock up,
but you're staying home.

56:04.703 --> 56:07.252
No one's going out
there until I say so.

56:07.706 --> 56:08.878
<i>VARGAS: Man down,
he's got Falco.</i>

56:08.999 --> 56:10.216
<i>MAN: Compromise, compromise.</i>

56:10.292 --> 56:11.259
<i>BOSS:
How the fuck did he do that?</i>

56:11.335 --> 56:13.303
<i>VARGAS: Never ever saw him, man.
He was right here and I never...</i>

56:13.379 --> 56:14.426
BOSS: <i>What about</i>
<i>the ship? Is he on it?</i>

56:14.505 --> 56:16.507
<i>VARGAS: He's not coming for the
ships, he's coming for fucking us!</i>

56:16.590 --> 56:18.183
<i>Just fucking shoot!
Shoot!</i>

56:21.220 --> 56:22.847
(AIR HISSING)

56:26.517 --> 56:28.269
One night, three dead.

56:29.019 --> 56:30.737
Not sure
I'm loving this trend.

56:31.438 --> 56:32.610
Two dead, one missing.

56:32.690 --> 56:34.158
Exactly.
Three dead.

56:34.233 --> 56:36.861
Well, look at it
this way, boys.

56:39.238 --> 56:41.115
We might all fit
on one ship now.

56:41.198 --> 56:42.290
SANTANA: Diaz!

56:46.954 --> 56:48.831
Get those other
traps back there.

56:49.456 --> 56:53.632
Luna, say something Bible-like
over these bodies.

57:03.846 --> 57:05.598
Okay, maybe,

57:07.266 --> 57:09.109
we zero this out.

57:11.186 --> 57:12.733
What is your tag anyway?

57:13.272 --> 57:15.195
So now you wanna know my name.

57:17.985 --> 57:19.737
Well, I'm not sure
I'm gonna say.

57:19.903 --> 57:22.907
Because everyone you know by
name, Santana, winds up dead.

57:26.118 --> 57:27.586
You gonna clean this shit up?

57:29.121 --> 57:30.839
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

57:31.582 --> 57:33.710
(GRUNTING)
(GROANING)

57:33.792 --> 57:35.214
(SANTANA CONTINUES GROANING)

57:37.171 --> 57:38.844
MAN: Excuse me.
Wow.

57:39.256 --> 57:41.429
Watch out for
surprise attacks.

57:42.301 --> 57:43.393
SANTANA: Maybe...

57:44.136 --> 57:48.061
Maybe it's time to start
merging assets, right?

57:48.140 --> 57:49.141
(CHUCKLES WEAKLY)

57:50.684 --> 57:52.607
So this is you
asking for my help?

57:53.020 --> 57:56.399
This is me saying that I may
need some of your gear.

57:58.150 --> 58:01.905
If some of your guys happen to
come attached to that gear,

58:02.613 --> 58:06.618
I will understand
that's the way it's gotta be.

58:08.118 --> 58:09.995
So you're asking
for my gear's help?

58:10.788 --> 58:12.210
More like that.

58:13.290 --> 58:14.507
Moss...

58:21.632 --> 58:24.101
The gear's saying, "Nah."
Bitch.

58:24.968 --> 58:26.436
There's your answer.

58:26.512 --> 58:28.640
What the fuck
do you want, man?

58:28.806 --> 58:32.106
You know what? I'm gonna
fold you in, Santana.

58:32.476 --> 58:36.447
But I give orders to Dahl. And
Delhi's gonna give orders to you.

58:36.730 --> 58:39.609
And that's the chain of command
from this point forward.

58:40.150 --> 58:42.824
Why am I not
loving this plan so far?

58:44.029 --> 58:46.657
Oh, I know, I know.
You know why?

58:46.824 --> 58:49.293
Because it sucks ass
and swallows!

58:49.827 --> 58:52.376
I'm not taking orders
from your pet whore

58:52.454 --> 58:53.922
who thinks I won't
smack her right back...

58:53.997 --> 58:55.749
(GRUNTS)
(GROANS)

58:56.667 --> 58:58.294
I don't fuck guys.

58:59.336 --> 59:01.839
Occasionally I fuck 'em up
if they need it.

59:04.508 --> 59:07.728
Here's what's gonna happen, Santana.
You're gonna take a back seat.

59:08.011 --> 59:09.854
We'll track Riddick
down, I promise.

59:10.389 --> 59:12.016
But I want him alive.

59:12.349 --> 59:16.229
You give me a day, and after
that he's yours to kill.

59:16.854 --> 59:18.606
You're giving me the bounty?

59:18.689 --> 59:22.739
You pay my crew, fuel costs,
the rest is yours. That's the deal.

59:24.361 --> 59:28.457
What is Riddick for you?
Not just some convict.

59:28.866 --> 59:31.494
What do you want?
Why are you here?

59:31.952 --> 59:33.078
Who are you?

59:34.454 --> 59:35.706
My name is Johns.

59:36.081 --> 59:38.425
Lock down those ships,
get those hogs on deck.

59:38.500 --> 59:40.423
I will ride with
Moss and Lockspur.

59:40.502 --> 59:44.723
I want a non-lethal load-out, L.O.D.'s
and phosphor frags to start with.

59:44.798 --> 59:48.723
This is a man that hunts by night.
We'll take it to him by day.

59:50.053 --> 59:53.398
Diaz! Vargas! Show me the
spot of the last kill.

59:56.727 --> 59:58.229
LOCKSPUR:
Some kind of canine.

01:00:11.241 --> 01:00:13.710
Hey, Diaz, I got a dog here.

01:00:14.202 --> 01:00:17.172
Is it the same dingo-dongo
thing from last night?

01:00:17.581 --> 01:00:19.128
Nah, I'm pretty sure
we killed that one.

01:00:26.757 --> 01:00:28.259
Could be the same one.

01:00:28.842 --> 01:00:29.889
The same.

01:00:29.968 --> 01:00:32.687
Dahl, get your sniper rifle
and barium rounds now.

01:00:44.483 --> 01:00:45.951
JOHNS: 1,500 meters.

01:00:55.452 --> 01:00:56.578
(BARKING)

01:00:59.247 --> 01:01:01.124
(SNARLING)

01:01:07.130 --> 01:01:08.131
(GROWLING)

01:01:12.719 --> 01:01:13.971
(BEEPING)

01:01:31.989 --> 01:01:33.286
(BEEPING)

01:01:58.807 --> 01:02:00.855
Could be just the first hole it found.
(BEEPING)

01:02:01.435 --> 01:02:04.609
A stressed animal is gonna
run to ground it knows.

01:02:06.106 --> 01:02:08.950
Besides,
I'm getting human pheromones.

01:03:32.317 --> 01:03:33.660
Riddick!

01:03:40.951 --> 01:03:42.999
Dial down,
dial down, dial down!

01:03:50.961 --> 01:03:52.213
LOCKSPUR:
Santana's guy.

01:03:52.295 --> 01:03:53.342
MOSS: Falco.

01:03:53.421 --> 01:03:55.389
LOCKSPUR: Shit.
Did we just kill a hostage?

01:03:55.465 --> 01:03:57.217
JOHNS: I've been hunting
Riddick for 10 years.

01:03:57.467 --> 01:04:00.311
The concept of a hostage
has no appeal to him.

01:04:00.387 --> 01:04:02.264
Falco was already dead.

01:04:02.764 --> 01:04:05.859
This is just some fucking
sideshow to buy more time.

01:04:08.520 --> 01:04:10.568
(JACKAL SNARLING)
JOHNS: Whoa! Fuck...

01:04:11.648 --> 01:04:12.991
Shit.

01:04:13.358 --> 01:04:14.575
(PANTING)

01:04:16.403 --> 01:04:18.246
Just dropped some
mud right there.

01:04:19.406 --> 01:04:21.500
So if Riddick isn't here...

01:05:01.948 --> 01:05:05.703
Dahl? Dahl, do you copy?
Does anyone copy?

01:05:06.536 --> 01:05:07.958
Dahl, you there?

01:06:03.927 --> 01:06:05.099
MAN: Boom.

01:06:05.178 --> 01:06:06.430
(MAKES KISSING NOISE)

01:06:09.057 --> 01:06:11.025
Were you just perving out
on me somehow?

01:06:11.768 --> 01:06:14.612
May all your dreams
come true, baby.

01:06:16.273 --> 01:06:19.698
You've got two minutes. I want
you out on fucking watch.

01:06:25.573 --> 01:06:26.699
Luna!

01:06:31.788 --> 01:06:35.634
Don't watch me. Watch my back.
That's what you're here for.

01:06:36.459 --> 01:06:38.928
Take two steps forward.
Two.

01:06:44.134 --> 01:06:45.306
(WHIRRING)

01:06:49.472 --> 01:06:51.691
Remember,
he could be anywhere.

01:07:42.400 --> 01:07:44.744
<i>(ON RADIO) This is Johns to
any-goddamn-body at the station.</i>

01:07:45.362 --> 01:07:49.492
<i>I want you to keep an eye on that locker.
Keep an eye on the node.</i>

01:07:49.949 --> 01:07:52.327
<i>Riddick may have
made an end run.</i>

01:07:52.911 --> 01:07:56.757
<i>My ETA is seven minutes.
But watch your back.</i>

01:08:06.424 --> 01:08:08.301
All right,
you little bitch.

01:08:08.385 --> 01:08:09.386
(COCKS GUN)

01:08:10.470 --> 01:08:13.269
Your two minutes are up. You
gonna do what I tell you to do?

01:08:14.265 --> 01:08:16.893
Rumor is Riddick
might be in the vicinity.

01:08:17.102 --> 01:08:19.651
Thought I should just
check on the locker.

01:08:21.356 --> 01:08:25.827
Get outside, get on your optics,
and get after this fucker!

01:08:26.444 --> 01:08:28.537
You're not
gonna find him here.

01:08:33.410 --> 01:08:35.037
(GRUNTING)
(GROANING)

01:08:37.455 --> 01:08:38.546
(SCREAMS)

01:08:39.457 --> 01:08:40.457
(GRUNTING)

01:08:41.542 --> 01:08:45.764
Actually, Dahl, I think we
have something in common.

01:08:46.714 --> 01:08:49.558
I don't fuck guys either.

01:08:49.716 --> 01:08:50.684
(YELLING)

01:08:50.760 --> 01:08:52.511
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:09:29.466 --> 01:09:31.059
(DEVICES BUZZING)

01:09:34.929 --> 01:09:36.727
You need to see this.

01:09:45.398 --> 01:09:46.524
He wrote that?

01:09:47.609 --> 01:09:50.988
He took out our deep space
communications. All of it.

01:09:51.779 --> 01:09:55.079
And whose blood is that?
There... Here...

01:09:55.783 --> 01:09:57.410
Over there...

01:10:02.707 --> 01:10:05.460
I had to kick
his ass again. Sorry.

01:10:06.836 --> 01:10:07.962
Not really.

01:10:08.171 --> 01:10:09.172
(CHUCKLES)

01:10:11.633 --> 01:10:12.634
(DOOR CREAKS)

01:10:16.012 --> 01:10:17.104
Fuck it.

01:10:18.515 --> 01:10:20.734
Let's take a look at this.

01:10:25.396 --> 01:10:27.273
(BEEPING AND CLICKING)

01:10:32.153 --> 01:10:33.370
Stop.

01:10:36.032 --> 01:10:37.534
That key leave your neck?

01:10:39.536 --> 01:10:40.537
Never.

01:10:40.954 --> 01:10:42.706
Well, the only reason
to write "fair trade"

01:10:43.540 --> 01:10:46.635
is if he got into that locker
and he took something out.

01:10:46.709 --> 01:10:50.054
Something that we need,
like a power node,

01:10:50.171 --> 01:10:53.266
which he could then swap
for something he needs.

01:10:54.217 --> 01:10:56.515
All that?
Wow.

01:10:57.053 --> 01:10:59.226
Highly unlikely.

01:11:01.140 --> 01:11:03.108
Let me join the fucking dots
for you, Santana.

01:11:03.184 --> 01:11:04.902
Here's what I'm saying. If
he did get in there somehow,

